n. This operator is strongly  related to the notion of dynamic extent which we denotationally characterize.  Some programming examples are commented and we also show how to express  previously proposed control operators. A suggested implementation is  eventually discussed.</p><p><u>Downloads:</u></p><ul><li><a href="http://www-spi.lip6.fr/~queinnec/Papers/popl6.ps.gz">ps</a></li><li><a href="http://www-spi.lip6.fr/~queinnec/PDF/popl6.pdf">pdf</a></li></ul><p><u>Bibtex citation:</u></p><pre>@inproceedings{
   key = "Que:Que91a"
   author = "Christian Queinnec and Bernard Serpette"
   title = "A Dynamic Extent Control Operator for Partial Continuations"
   booktitle = "POPL '91 - Eighteenth Annual ACM symposium on Principles of Programming Languages"
   pages = "174-184"
   month = "January"
   year = "1991"
   url = "http://www-spi.lip6.fr/~queinnec/Papers/popl6.ps.gz"
   url = "http://www-spi.lip6.fr/~queinnec/PDF/popl6.pdf"
}
